RESOLUTION & TOGGLES
widgets_values:
--------------------------------------------------------------

*Resolution - T2V*

- T2V mode consists of a small list of standard resolution presets, I will add entries more WAN targeted entries in the future.

- Resolution can be overriden by setting "override_width" and "override_height".

--------------------------------------------------------------

*Resolution - I2V*

- I2V mode consumes an input image and scales it to match the pixel count of standard WAN resolutions (1280x720, 480x854), while maintaining the original aspect ratio.

- "Native" will pass the image through without scaling.

- Resolution can be overriden by setting "override_width" and "override_height".

--------------------------------------------------------------

*Toggle Upscale and Interpolation*

- Allows for toggling upscaling and interpolation. They are not interdependent (you can upscale but not interpolate & vice versa).

--------------------------------------------------------------

*Toggle Intelligent Face Detection & Drift Correction*

- Allows for enabling and disabling of the intelligent best face frame detection, and correcting for drift.

- Drift is introduced when the best face frame further back than the last frame, and is automatically corrected for within this workflow while face detection is enabled. Drift correction will run X number of additonal segments until it is at or over your desired "total_length" while respecting your segment length.

--------------------------------------------------------------

*Frames to Check for Face (from Last Frame)*

- Limits how many frames back the face detection functionality is allowed to probe.

--------------------------------------------------------------

*Video Execution ID*

- A unique ID the DaxNodes video segment generation uses on the backend for segment tracing. These segments get written to "/output/.tmp/<execution_id>/xyz123.mp4".

- Leaving this value the same will cause the manager to overwrite old segments under the same execution ID with new ones (but will not delete other old ones if segment number lower, resulting in older segments being stitched after newer ones - just something to keep in mind). I would recommend just incrementing it by 1 as you finish working on videos.

- It is recommended to clean out "/output/.tmp/" every once in a while to conserve space.
--------------------------------------------------------------

nodes.title: PROMPTING
widgets_values:
--------------------------------------------------------------

*Persistent Positive Prompt*

- Passed for each segment generated, does not change.

- Should represent consistent details in the video.

*Example*:

-----
A woman with green eyes and brown hair in her warmly lit bedroom.
-----

--------------------------------------------------------------

*Segment Positive Prompts*

- Separated with "+"

- Will only process the number of prompts to match your number of segments. (ie. "segment_length" = 5s, "total_length" = 15s: 3 segment prompts)

- Each prompt should be roughly targeted to fit within your "segment_length", but you can of course do something like;

*Example*:

-----
She is <starting action> + She is <continuing action>
-----

OR

-----
She is writing in a journal. + She closes the journal and stands up. + She walks away.
-----

--------------------------------------------------------------

- Brainstorming better ways to handle this in future versions, but think this is pretty good for now.

- WAN sometimes like to add camera movement directly at the beginning of segments, you can mitigate this with persistent prompts like "A single, unmoving <wide-angle, close-up, etc...> shot, The camera remains fixed and steady throughout.", or prompting for specific movement in the segments themselves.

--------------------------------------------------------------
